CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 25, 1953, pg. 11 reads: "United In Catholic Rites - Lieut. and Mrs. Robert Joseph Cameron are shown leaving the altar in Church of Our Lady of the Blessed Sacrament in Pittsburgh, Pa., where they were united in marriage. The bride is the former Miss Jacqueline Peeler, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Melvin Eugene Peeler of Bricelyn Street, who gave a sparkling party following the ritual, on the Peeler lawn, where a specially constructed patio made a handsome setting for the many guests. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Peeler-Cameron wedding party with six men, including groom Robert Joseph Cameron wearing U.S. Army uniform, and five women, including bride Jacqueline Peeler Cameron wearing gown with floral sheer overlay and matching veil, posed on lawn of Mr. and Mrs. Melvin Eugene Peeler, Bricelyn Street, another version
